<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /><a href="https://1.bp.blogspot.com/-y9hJ0ToaGXw/Xzv71wq4puI/AAAAAAAAAsg/jpjNNLxPLLIekICwsGtf2LXNHDPd1GeHwCLcBGAsYHQ/s2048/library_2017.jpg" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img alt="library" border="0" data-original-height="1382" data-original-width="2048" height="270" src="https://1.bp.blogspot.com/-y9hJ0ToaGXw/Xzv71wq4puI/AAAAAAAAAsg/jpjNNLxPLLIekICwsGtf2LXNHDPd1GeHwCLcBGAsYHQ/w400-h270/library_2017.jpg" width="400" /></a></div>&nbsp;

<p></p>

<span style="font-family: arial;"><p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: x-small;"><span><b>"What we really need is not more authors,<br /></b></span><b><span>&nbsp;<span>or better publishers. What we most need is<br /></span></span></b><span style="font-family: arial;"><b>&nbsp;a vastly better system to identify the books we will love.<span>"</span></b></span></span><span style="font-family: arial;"><br /></span></p><div style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://techcrunch.com/2016/01/16/book-it-baby/" style="color: #b4445c;" target="_blank"><span style="font-size: x-small;">TechCrunch</span></a></div></span>

<p style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-size: medium;"><span style="background-color: white; color: #111111; font-family: arial;">Beantown Web has developed such a system. For the 10th year running Beantown Web has conducted a quasi-scientific meta-search to identify the best business books published during the calendar year.&nbsp;</span><span style="background-color: #fefdfa; color: #333333; font-family: arial;">These books are most likely to add value to your career.</span></span></p><p style="text-align: left;"><span style="background-color: white; color: #111111; font-family: arial;"><span style="background-color: #fefdfa; color: #333333; font-size: medium;">This year's search began by identifying 13 "Best of" lists. This resource list is available upon request. Presented here are the results.</span></span></p><p style="text-align: left;"><span style="background-color: white; color: #111111; font-family: arial;"><span style="font-size: medium;">A total of 113 books were mentioned on at least one "Best of" list -- 74 of these books were mentioned only once.</span><br /><span style="font-size: x-small;"><br /></span></span></p><div style="background-color: white;">

<h3 style="margin: 10px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left;">
<span style="font-family: arial; font-size: large;">The Honorable Mention Shelf</span></h3><span style="color: #111111; font-family: arial;"><p style="text-align: left;"><span><span style="font-size: medium;">An additional 19 books were mentioned on two lists and these books comprise the </span><b style="font-size: large;">Honorable Mention</b><span style="font-size: medium;"> list.</span><br /><span style="font-size: x-small;"><br /></span></span></p></span></div>

<h3 style="background-color: white; margin: 10px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left;">
<span style="font-family: arial; font-size: large;">The Must-Read Shelf</span></h3><div style="background-color: white;">
<span style="color: #111111; font-family: arial; font-size: medium;"><p style="text-align: left;">Eight books were mentioned on three lists and have been placed on the <b>Must-Read</b>&nbsp;shelf:</p></span></div>

<ul style="background-color: white; color: #111111;">

<li style="text-align: left;"><a href="https://www.harpercollins.com/9780062416049/barking-up-the-wrong-tree" target="_blank"><span style="font-family: arial; font-size: medium;">Barking Up the Wrong Tree</span></a></li>

